c:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Crowdin is best suited for open source projects, game developers, community translation, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Unbabel, meanwhile, shines for customer support teams, global companies, service desks, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2009, Crowdin describes itself as \"Collaborative localization platform with crowdsourcing and AI translation.\" Unbabel, established in 2013, positions itself as \"AI-powered translation combining machine translation with human editors.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
d:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Crowdin** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to more features (9 vs 7), availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean Unbabel is a poor choice — far from it. Unbabel excels in its own right, particularly for customer support teams and global companies.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value great crowdsourcing capabilities, go with Crowdin. If human-quality translation at scale matters more to you, Unbabel is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
